<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2244] Improve StandardTokenizer&apos;s understanding of non ASCII punctuation and quotes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2244</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;In the vein of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1126&quot; title=&quot;Simplify StandardTokenizer JFlex grammar&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1126&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1390&quot; title=&quot;add ASCIIFoldingFilter and deprecate ISOLatin1AccentFilter&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1390&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, StandardTokenizerImpl.jflex should do a better job at understanding non-ASCII punctuation characters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, its understanding of the single-quote character &quot;&apos;&quot; is currently limited to that character only. It will set a token&apos;s type to APOSTROPHE only if the &quot;&apos;&quot; was used.&lt;br/&gt;
In the patch attached, I added all the characters that ASCIIFoldingFilter would change into &quot;&apos;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure that this is the right approach so I didn&apos;t write a complete patch for all the other hardcoded characters used in jflex rules such as &quot;.&quot;, &quot;-&quot; which have some variants in ASCIIFoldingFilter that could be used as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe a better approach would be to make it possible to have an ASCIIFoldingFilter-like reader as a character filter that could be in inserted in front of StandardTokenizer ?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
